725734f-a.text: 94th Street at the S.E. corner of Thirty-Fifth Avenue (approximately the actual location of this house), showing three views of a small house which was the property of H. S. Leverich in 1860. The surrounding grounds seen in these views also belong to this individual. View one is probably taken from Junction Boulevard. 1923. Views 2 & 3: March 1923. Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

725738f-b.text: 94th Street, at the S.E. corner of Thirty-Fifth Avenue (approximately the actual location of this house), showing two views of a small house which belonged to H. S. Leverich in 1850.  It was demolished in May 1927. See other views for more data. March 1925. View 2: October 1925. Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
